      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAYTARA (8) won't find an easier race to get off the mark at start seven. Comes back a level after tiring in the straight with a battling fourth over 1550m at Canterbury. Will take control early and looks limited if she can't win this. VISION IN A DREAM (9) struck some trouble at the start and never travelled like a genuine chance as fav on debut with a battling fifth over 1200m at Gosford. Expected to give a glimpse of what she's capable of over this trip. ANGEL CITY (6) resumed in a three-horse field with a close-up third over 1400m in the heavy (9) going at Nowra. Showed ability when last in work and can play a leading role here. DAME DIVIDEND (7) unwanted in betting on resumption with a plugging sixth over 1200m at Gosford. Ready for this distance range and not to be overlooked.",
